    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:ital,wght@0,100;0,300;0,400;0,700;0,900;1,100;1,300;1,400;1,700;1,900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body class="w-full flex flex-col items-center leading-relaxed text-stone-800">
    <main>
      <div class="w-full max-w-2xl py-10 flex flex-col gap-9">
        <h1 class="text-2xl tracking-wide m-0">Ben Isenstein</h1>
        <section class="flex flex-col gap-5">
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I'm a full stack developer. I love crafting rich experiences for the web. I think <span class="italic">the web platform itself</span> is one of the coolest things there is, and I like to enable other devs and businesses to build for the web more effectively.</p>
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I live in Calgary, Alberta, Canada. I travel throughout the Americas to visit friends, climb mountains, dance, and play music.</p>
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I spent four years as a musician, completing a bachelors degree in jazz piano. Now I bring a sense of deep observation, creativity, and collaboration to my work in tech.</p>
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I regularly conduct talks and "ask-me-anythings" at <a class="font-bold text-black" href="https://www.inceptionu.com/" target="_blank">InceptionU</a>, my alma mater bootcamp in Calgary. Growing up, I often found myself in environments where direct mentorship was plentiful. Music teachers, coaches, summer camp leaders - I believe giving and receiving mentorship makes communities, organizations and teams much stronger.</p>
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I consulted full-time for Canadian pension <a class="font-bold text-black" href="https://www.omers.com/" target="_blank">OMERS</a> via agency <a class="font-bold text-black" href="https://www.devtheory.com/" target="_blank">DevTheory</a> from 2022-2024.</p>
          <p class="p-0 m-0">I'm currently nomadic in South America.</p>
        </section>
